  <description akvo:type="6" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SSID is implmenting partner as part of ACT appeal HTI161, but since this runs until October 6th, 2017 and no revision has been received as yet, this contract will be made directly with SSID. The project may possibly become part of an ACT appeal. If it does not, then SSID will come up with a destination for the 3 % funding for ACT ICF which is at present part of their budget.
Narrative summary of planned intervention 
Responding to the adverse effects caused by Hurricane Mathew to agriculture, animals and houses in Ganthier, towns located in the department of Ouest, Haiti, is extremely important to support the most affected families.

The SSID is to accompany and support the beneficiary families in improving their state of life after Hurricane Mathew, by providing seeds for farming short-cycle products such as cereals and legumes; as well as delivery of animals (goats-sheep-pig) for breeding as a means of generating income.  Also will support with the construction of 8 homes flooded by Mathew.With these actions we seek to respond to the objectives and purposes of contributing to the improvement of the living conditions in which a large number of Haitian families develop, which have seen their situation worsen with the adverse effects of the Mathew storm and poor weather conditions that have continued to occur in the coverage area.

The project is aimed at a maximum of 87 families from 7 communities (neighborhoods) of the Municipality of Ganthier. Of these families 7 would benefit from the construction of their houses. Also, 50 families will benefit from animals for breeding (20 with goats, 20 with sheep and 10 with pigs) and 30 families with the supply of vegetable seeds and cereals (Onion, Okra, Beet, Carrot, Bean, Eggplant, Leek, Chili, tomato, Corn and Sorghum)</narrative>
  </description>
